God's Calendar

69/70 Ratio

Ancient calendars used a 360-day year and some continue to do so.  Did the Flood cause Earth's orbital period to change?  It's possible that catastrophic changes in Earth's crust during the Flood caused a change in Earth's orbital period from the initial 360-day year to the current length of a year.  But was this change random or did God divinely ordain an exact ratio?

(69/70) / (360/365.24219) = 1.0000679

In fact, the ratio 69/70 almost exactly relates a 360-day year to the current Solar year with a discrepancy of only 36 minutes.  There are multiple ways to measure a year and Earth's axial precession causes the length of a year to vary up to 30 minutes.  Accepting the current Mean Tropical Solar Year of 365.24219 days, which is based on a model, the 69/70 ratio is accurate to within 7 thousandths of 1 percent (70 ppm).  This is comparable to the tolerance of a quartz crystal oscillator used in a digital clock.  It's safe to say this 69/70 ratio could not occur by chance!

The unit of feet, passed down to the Greeks and Romans from the ancient Egyptians, appears to have been defined from a relationship between 360 and the length of a year.  If you're at the equator, a distance of 1/360 of Earth's circumference (also known as 1° of longitude) is 1000 feet multiplied by the length of a year.

62/70 Ratio

A 62/70 ratio closely relates the Full Moon Cycle (411.78443029 days) to the current Solar year.  A 69/70 ratio closely relates the Lunar Year (354.36707 days) to a 360-day year.  There is a half-day discrepancy in both Lunar ratios, which may relate to night-only observability of the Moon.  In any case, the Lunar ratios are accurate to at least 0.1%, which is more than statistically significant.

Prophecy of 7 + 62 + 1 Weeks in Daniel

Which Command and What Year?

Depending on who you listen to, the command to restore and rebuild Jerusalem might have been in 457 BC, 449 BC, or 444 BC.  One interesting result of these ratios is that no matter which calendar you happen to be using and which command event you use for a starting point, there are durations of either 62, 69, or 70 weeks of years pointing to significance right around the year that Jesus, Son of God, the Messiah was cut off, for you and I.

360-day Year 444 BC (69 * 7 * 360 days) - (444 - 1 year) 33 AD
Current Solar Year 449 BC (69 * 7 years) - (449 - 1 year) 35 AD
360-day Year 449 BC (70 * 7 * 360 days) - (449 - 1 year) 35 AD
411.78-day Lunar Cycle 457 BC (62 * 7 * 411.78443 days) - (457 - 1 year) 33 AD
Current Solar Year 457 BC (70 * 7 years) - (457 - 1 year) 34 AD

Why the extra -1 year? There is no "0 year", so we need to subtract one year.

A Stunning Revelation Could Mean Betelgeuse Is Set to Blow 

History of Measurements

American Association of Variable Star Observers (AAVSO) summarizes the history of measurements of Betelgeuse, also known as Alpha Orionis.  It's the second brightest star in the the constellation Orion, after Rigel.  It's interesting to note that a significant dip in brightness, similar to what was observed in 2019-2020, occurred approximately 72 years earlier around 1948, the year Israel became a nation.

Shrinking

The distance to Betelgeuse is difficult to determine from parallax (the change in apparent position in the sky) produced by the orbit of the Earth around the Sun, since it's brightness and shape vary on a cycle of approximately one year.  In 1920, Betelgeuse was the first star diameter measured by Albert A. Michelson with his interferometer.  Since that time, various attempts have been made to measure the distance to Betelgeuse, typically using parallax and various statistical methods to reduce error.

Nobel prize winning physicist Charles H. Townes (1915 – 2015), famous for helping invent the LASER, believed that Betelgeuse was shrinking, and at a rate secular astrophysicists were not willing to accept.  Charles Townes was a Christian and a Creationist, and likely understood the truth that the universe was created about 6000 years ago, rather than billions of years that secular astronomers believe.  As a professor at UC Berkeley, Townes used the Infrared Spatial Interferometer (ISI) on Mt. Wilson to record the diameter of Betelgeuse from 1993 to 2008, showing that the diameter had shrunk more than 15% over 15 years.

Townes published a paper with his diameter data (image source):

There is an interesting progression in historical calculations of the "distance" to Betelgeuse that would seem to line up with Townes' observation of a decreasing diameter.  If we assume, contrary to popular belief, that historical calculations were accurate and those values are graphed on a timeline, we can observe a consistent increase.  If the diameter of Betelgeuse is decreasing as Townes believed, then this apparent increase in "distance" may instead be related to a decrease in diameter. Distance and apparent size are inversely proportional, so a column has been added showing "distance" values inverted (normalized to the first value) and proportional to diameter.  We can see that these numbers show a decrease roughly in agreement with the 15% decrease measured by Townes between 1993 and 2008.

Year Distance (Light years) Observation Inverse Normalized (1/x) * 163

The inverted values appear to fall into two sets which each describe a surprisingly smooth negative slope.  The difference between the two slopes is not clear, but may be related to similar distance measurement techniques being used.

Magog Invasion

Modern warfare described in an ancient language

It's interesting that the Hebrew words for warfare used in Ezekiel 38 & 39 are purely functional.  It's only by inference that you can connect these to physical objects.  As a result, a translation using modern object names could be made that would be fully literal and maintain the same equivalence and accuracy as a translation using ancient object names.

Ezekiel 38:1-6

Now the word of the LORD came to me, saying, “Son of man, set your face against Gog [or Goth], of the land of Magog [or Magoth], the prince of Rosh [or Ros, like Rosatom, Roscosmos], Meshech, and Tubal, and prophesy against him, and say, ‘Thus says the Lord GOD: “Behold, I am against [literal: an opposition force] you, O Gog, the prince of Rosh, Meshech, and Tubal. I will turn you around [literal: return to place, similar to making u-turn], put hooks into your jaws, and lead you out [literal: leave your place], with all your army, horses [literal: skip like a swallow; could describe swallow-shaped fighter aircraft], and horsemen [literal: stretched/partitioned fighting vehicle, root word can involve piecing/stinging], all splendidly [literal: perfect] clothed [literal: wrap around], a great company with bucklers [literal: shield with opposing sensation/prick, similar meaning to reactive armor] and shields [literal:  shield or covering (subtle, background), similar meaning to stealth], all of them handling [literal: external attachment; could describe a pylon or hardpoint mount] swords [literal: piercing weapon, laying waste; could describe bunker-buster weapons]. Persia [Iran], Ethiopia [Ethiopia, Sudan], and Libya [Libya!] are with them, all of them with shield [literal:  shield or covering (subtle, background), similar meaning to stealth] and helmet [literal: high round]; Gomer [uncertain, probably includes Turkey] and all its troops; the house of Togarmah [Turkey] from the far north and all its troops—many people are with you.

Ezekiel 38:7-9

“Prepare yourself and be ready, you and all your companies that are gathered about you; and be a guard for them. After many days you will be visited. In the latter years [literal: end times, future, last days] you will come into the land of those brought back from the sword and gathered from many people on the mountains of Israel, which had long been desolate; they were brought out of the nations, and now all of them dwell safely. You will ascend [literal: lift, up, depart, actively mount, similar meaning to takeoff], coming like a storm [literal: rush over, destroy], covering [literal: come down on] the land like a cloud [literal: covering the sky, in transit], you and all your troops [literal: impending, wing, army] and many peoples with you.”

Eze 38:10

‘Thus says the Lord GOD: “On that day it shall come to pass that thoughts [literal: speech] will arise [literal: on] in your mind, and you will make an evil plan: you will say, ‘I will go up [literal: lift, up, depart, actively mount, similar meaning to takeoff] against a land of unwalled villages [literal: town without walls]; I will go to [literal: come down on] a peaceful [at rest in the land following wars, first used in Joshua] people, who dwell safely [literal: confidently], all of them dwelling without walls [without walls: houses that may be redeemed, released in Jubilee], and having neither bars nor gates’ [literals: barred, door, or shut door, maybe implying post-Rapture?] — to take plunder [šālal šālāl literal: spoil the spoil, to strip off] and to take booty [bāzaz baz literal: prey on the prey;  first usage of both confidently and prey is in Gen 34:25-27], to stretch out your hand against the waste places that are again inhabited, and against a people gathered from the nations, who have acquired livestock and goods, who dwell in the midst of the land. Sheba, Dedan, the merchants of Tarshish, and all their young lions will say to you, ‘Have you come to take plunder? Have you gathered your army to take booty, to carry away silver and gold, to take away livestock and goods, to take great plunder?’ ” ’

Ezekiel 38 & 39:
Verse Summary Comment
Ez 38:1-6, Ez 39:1-2

Gog, of the land of Magog, the prince of Rosh, Meshech, Tubal, Persia, Ethiopia, and Libya
  • Russia and the former Soviet states are far north of Israel; the Scythian people groups north of the Caucasus mountains.  Gog and Magog or Goth and Magoth may refer to people groups of Gothic descent.  There is an island of Gogland east of St. Petersburg.  Some connect Gog with Ukraine.

  • The Persians and Medes both descended from ancient Iranian peoples in the region of modern Iran.

  • Ethiopian and Libyan peoples include much of northeastern Africa, including Sudan and Eritrea.

  • There seems to be a 2-step process: Russia is blocked and turned around, then forced (maybe unwillingly) to attack Israel as the head of a coalition.
  • Russia (Magog) is also pointed out as being a guard to other members of the coalition.  Increasingly, Russia is acting as a guard against the emerging global order for Iran and many of the African nations.  Additionally, economically guarding China and India, through BRICS.
